snippet.textDisplay: The "Hong Kong style" tart is actually the "Macau style" egg custard tart. Macau was a portugese colony untill 1999 and they are GOOD at making these tarts, with their own twist. Hong Kong people like to go to Macau (it is actually an hour boat trip from HK, probably less by car) to gamble in the casinos and liked the pasteis de nata so much that brought them to HK.

Curiosity:
Here in Brazil we usually call the "Pastéis de Nata" as "Pastéis de Belém", but in Portugal you can only name it that way if you're in the City of Belém. Elsewhere u can't be calling it as "Pastéis de Belém", the real name of the food, since it was created there.
